   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The Budget Management module is a cost budgeting utility. It enables  project practitioners to track the estimated  budget   of the associated project. Also, this provides the   ability to determine the best spending plan for the project. The budget information is available in  <ph conref="../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.dita#reference-9043/product_name"
             class="- topic/ph "/> through data integration with  EBS. </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <xref href="Budget_Estimates/BEs.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Budget  Estimates</xref>: The budget  estimate displays  the overall cost of project implementation. On receiving the project  budget details from EBS into   <ph conref="../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.dita#reference-9043/product_name"
             class="- topic/ph "/>, the    <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Budget Estimates</uicontrol> records are automatically created and approved.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <xref href="Accessing_All_Forecast_Records.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Forecasts</xref>: Once the budget of the project is estimated,  a forecast is automatically created and approved during data integration with  EBS. </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <xref href="Budget_Estimate_Revision/ReviseBE.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Budget  Estimate Revision</xref>: The changes in budget are recorded in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Budget Estimate Revision</uicontrol> form. </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <xref href="Vw_the_Cur_Bud.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Current Budget  Estimate</xref>: The  page displays the latest approved budget estimate and all of its approved revisions.</p>
